Defendant Tayetta S Currin in court with attorney Michael M Krill.  Michelle L Viste, Asst Atty General appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  The court have reviewed all materials that have been submitted.  Statements to the court from the state, defense and defendant.
As to EACH count, concurrent:  Court sentenced the defendant to serve 6 months in the House of Correction; credit for 0 days served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 2 YEARS, concurrent with the following conditions:
-Follow all rules of probation.
-No further violations of the law.
-Assessment and any treatment.
-Maintain full-time employment.
-No contact with ST or ROA.
-Pay restitution of $5000.00, $2500.00 per year of probation and NO LESS THAN $200 per month to Department of Justice Medicaid Fraud Unit, 17 W. Main St., PO Box 7857, Madison, WI 53707
-Pay victim witness surcharge and all costs, assessments and surcharges.
FAILURE TO PAY ALL COSTS, ASSESSMENTS, SURCHARGES AND RESTITUTION AS ORDERED WILL RESULT IN CIVIL JUDGMENT.
